Deepak yadav
What is standard size of cube and why it is?
EB
17:29
Er. Brijesh
In reply to this message
Why is the size of a standard cement concrete cube fixed as 150mm?

150mm cube is appropriate size for most types of concretes mix designs due to homogeneity of mix, which will give repeatable and reliable concrete strength results. You donтАЩt want a cube dimension such that it may give misleading or non reproducible results.
For example if your concrete mix has maximum aggregate dimension of 37.5 mm and two such aggregates lay side by side in a cube prepared for testing, then 150mm side cube will give a more representative value of concrete strength than a cube of say 100mm side. You can see that in the case of 100mm side cube, 75mm out of 100mm will consist of only aggregates which may cause the cube to fail due to crushing/ slippage of aggregate alone, however, 150mm side cube will not have such a problem and hence will give correct concrete strength.
